tldr: The project involved implementing a database for questionnaire responses,
  building a simple admin dashboard with CSV export, and setting up
  password-based authentication. The authentication system was later simplified
  using Next.js middleware for cleaner route protection.
overview: The user wanted to add database functionality and an admin dashboard
  to their sleep questionnaire application. After evaluating the existing
  codebase, a plan was created to implement a PostgreSQL database (NeonDB) for
  storing questionnaire responses, including denormalized demographic data. An
  admin dashboard was developed with a login page, a table to view responses,
  and a CSV export feature. The authentication system was initially designed
  with custom session management but was later simplified to leverage Next.js
  middleware for more efficient route protection and a basic cookie-based
  session. The database schema was successfully pushed, and the core
  functionalities were verified through direct API calls and browser testing,
  confirming data submission and retrieval.
